 Plateau, respectively. The proto-Philippine Sea\nbasin was trapped as a sinistral transpressional pop-up structure at a position\nthat was 20{\\deg}south of its present position. While the Japan arc migrated\neastward during the rifting period of the Japan Sea basin, the Shikoku Basin\nopened and the Parece Vela Basin widened.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 21 Nov 2012 16:27:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-02-20"}
