 primary component could have been a classical Be star.\nNeither can be firmly excluded, but for Roche lobe overflow to occur, a\ncombination of stellar and orbital parameter extremawould be required.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 21 Nov 2012 21:08:20 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-01-09"}
